[1] Cholera - Ghana (Central Region)
Date: Tue, 11 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: GhanaWeb [edited]
<http://www.ghanaweb.com/GhanaHomePage/regional/artikel.php?ID=107109>

Dr Nii Adjetey, Assin North District Director of Health Services, on Mon,
10 Jul 2006, deplored the insanitary conditions under which most food
vendors operate within the district. He said this had resulted in an
outbreak of cholera within the district, with 40 cases including the death
of a person, recorded within the past 2 weeks.
Dr Adjetey therefore advised the public to desist from buying food from
such vendors and asked the women to ensure clean and healthy surroundings
both at home and where they sell their wares. He stressed that they should
desist from exposing food items to flies and dust.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
