[2] Cholera - India (Gujarat)
Date: Wed, 12 Jul 2006
From: ProMED-mail <promed@promedmail.org>
Source: Ahmedabad Newsline [edited]
<http://cities.expressindia.com/fullstory.php?newsid=192576>

Four more cholera cases were reported positive after tests, taking the
total count of cholera-affected in Chhani village to 9. Those reported to
be suffering from the disease were residents of susceptible areas like
Bhathuji Nagar, Swaminarayan Faliya, Anjana Farm, as were the earlier
cases. However, health officials said that the patients were not in a
critical condition and were stable.
Chhani Nagarpalika administrator Kiran Desai said that the village was
declared cholera-hit by Vadodara collector Rajiv Topno, in view of the
health situation. Caused by a failure in the functioning of the
chlorination plant and leakages in the water network, the situation in the
village had aggravated with around 100-odd patients seeking treatment at
the Chhani Community Health Center on Mon, 10 Jul 2006.
--
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>
